# Frontend UI Rules

- Favor expressive, premium UI over generic dashboard layouts.
- Reuse the existing shared component layer and theme tokens before adding new abstractions.
- Keep animations purposeful and not purely decorative.
- Respect the current multilingual structure and locale-aware navigation.
- Distinguish between implemented features and roadmap ideas in UI copy and states.
- Do not redesign existing screens or global styles unless requested.
- Maintain accessibility basics: semantic elements, icon button labels, keyboard support, and clear focus behavior.
- Prefer minimal structural changes over large UI rewrites.
- Prefer semantic markup and logical heading structure for crawlable, accessible pages.
- Preserve or improve metadata, content clarity, and performance when touching public-facing UI.
- Avoid heavy motion or visual effects that harm usability, reduced-motion comfort, or page performance.
